- You're talking about my ear.

28:52.399 --> 28:53.939
Come on. Don't start with the ear again.

28:54.025 --> 28:55.235
- Not the ear story.
- The ear story, not again.

28:55.360 --> 28:57.360
- We all know the ear story.
- We don't want to hear the ear story.

28:57.445 --> 28:59.855
- We all know I wrestled in college.
- Right.

28:59.948 --> 29:04.448
A common injury associated with that sport
is trauma to the ear, a clot.

29:05.036 --> 29:08.156
Which, if left unattended,
causes a contraction in the cartilage

29:08.373 --> 29:10.423
and forms cauliflower ears.

29:10.667 --> 29:14.127
My college roommate used to bring up
my ear configuration all the time.

29:14.421 --> 29:17.131
Parties, social events, you name it.

29:17.465 --> 29:19.925
That didn't really bother me all that much
because he's usually bragging about

29:20.009 --> 29:22.759
how my ears are a badge of courage.

29:23.763 --> 29:25.973
- Made me a little less self-conscious.
- Of course it would.

29:26.641 --> 29:27.731
But that was short-lived.

29:28.560 --> 29:31.770
One morning, during spring break,
I hear him on the phone, bagging on me,

29:31.896 --> 29:34.016
talking about my "queer ear."

29:36.401 --> 29:37.651
You see something funny?

29:37.735 --> 29:39.025
Sorry, go ahead.

29:39.654 --> 29:43.624
So I realize I'd become the brunt of a joke
simply because I look a little bit different.

29:44.242 --> 29:46.492
So I decided to educate my roommate

29:46.578 --> 29:50.038
on the common decency that should be
afforded people who look a little different.

29:50.623 --> 29:53.333
I smashed him upside his goddamn head!

29:53.835 --> 29:55.165
Several times.

29:56.212 --> 29:59.012
Until he had a little cluster
of cauliflower all his own.

29:59.674 --> 30:02.724
- And your point is?
- It ain't easy being green.

30:04.679 --> 30:06.679
The fuck you think I'm talking about?

30:10.018 --> 30:13.058
Anyway, me and Christmas
are gonna head down to Vilena

30:13.146 --> 30:15.226
and scout the island
to see if we should take the job.

30:15.315 --> 30:18.025
How much we get paid?
I need more money for my family.

30:18.234 --> 30:20.574
What fucking family are you talking about?

30:22.864 --> 30:24.034
My family.

30:25.366 --> 30:26.366
You know, don't ask.

30:42.217 --> 30:44.047
Listen, that girl wasn't your type.

30:44.344 --> 30:45.604
Her loss, right?

30:45.845 --> 30:47.755
I should have broke that bastard's jaw.

30:47.847 --> 30:49.557
Maybe you were lucky.
He could have broke yours.

30:49.807 --> 30:53.477
- Impossible.
- You know, Christmas, I understand,

30:53.561 --> 30:56.561
but let's just say you were with her
for a couple of hours,

30:56.648 --> 30:58.478
and it's nice, and it's hot and heavy,

30:58.566 --> 31:00.356
but after that, think about it.

31:00.693 --> 31:02.323
What do you do for the rest of the day?

31:02.904 --> 31:04.534
She probably did you a favor.

31:04.614 --> 31:07.244
Now you have more time
to feel sorry for yourself.

31:08.451 --> 31:09.791
You're a bleak bastard.

32:14.267 --> 32:16.847
Morning. Morning.

32:19.981 --> 32:21.901
Morning! Speak English?

32:24.235 --> 32:25.315
Big plane, huh?

32:26.404 --> 32:29.244
Yeah, we use it to transport
injured animals.

32:29.324 --> 32:31.834
- Why are you here?
- Ornithologists.

32:31.993 --> 32:34.453
We're photographing exotic birds.

32:46.799 --> 32:47.879
You're nervous?

32:47.967 --> 32:49.217
Nervous?

32:50.678 --> 32:52.758
No. Why?

32:52.847 --> 32:54.557
You just look nervous.

32:55.058 --> 32:56.978
I'm not nervous. Do I look nervous?

32:58.770 --> 33:00.520
Your skin looks a little dry.

33:00.938 --> 33:02.148
That's because of the altitude.

33:02.231 --> 33:05.741
Well, it's not the altitude.
You fly with the window open all the time.

33:05.818 --> 33:08.028
- Dehydration.
- Yeah, it is dehydration.

33:08.112 --> 33:11.872
But there's ways to get around that.
There's new skin, it's like stem cell research.

33:12.116 --> 33:14.196
You are looking handsome.
Don't worry about it.

33:14.285 --> 33:16.075
- You're jealous?
- I'm a little jealous. Yeah.

33:16.204 --> 33:18.004
You're younger.
You have youth on your side.

33:18.539 --> 33:22.289
Overall, I'm happy to be myself. Are you?

33:22.835 --> 33:24.375
- So you're done.
- Done.

33:25.171 --> 33:26.961
- Good to know you.
- Good to know you.

33:27.048 --> 33:28.378
Yeah, we do this all the time.

33:28.966 --> 33:31.046
We kid ourselves.
That's how we stay awake on the plane.

33:31.302 --> 33:32.852
I'm the only one who stays awake
on the plane.

33:32.929 --> 33:35.179
- He's always sleeping.
- Yeah, you're right.

34:15.138 --> 34:17.768
- What's the address?
- Yeah, it's in my head.

34:18.057 --> 34:19.887
Do you wanna share it?

34:20.518 --> 34:22.438
It's the Gloria Cantina.

34:22.520 --> 34:25.440
So actually, Cantina Gloria in Spanish.

34:25.773 --> 34:27.983
Spanish. Who are you, Zorro?

34:29.694 --> 34:31.114
Army.

34:31.195 --> 34:32.485
- Shit.
- Come on.

34:32.572 --> 34:33.822
In there.

34:52.300 --> 34:54.470
- You rolling?
- No, I'm on holiday.

34:57.722 --> 34:59.772
You, you, move the truck!

35:04.437 --> 35:05.937
Get the suit. Tighten up on the suit.

35:06.022 --> 35:07.272
Got him.

35:14.155 --> 35:16.905
Look at these clowns,
hand-picked monkeys.

35:27.335 --> 35:28.495
What's wrong with this picture?

35:31.214 --> 35:32.474
Everything.

35:33.090 --> 35:34.510
Let's get out of here.

35:36.010 --> 35:37.350
No, that's the point, you know.

35:37.470 --> 35:39.890
You think you know someone,
and you truly do not.

35:39.972 --> 35:42.982
Aren't you the guy who said,
"The man who best gets along with women

35:43.059 --> 35:45.019
"is the man who can
get along without them"?

35:45.102 --> 35:46.942
No, no. You're so not listening.

35:47.188 --> 35:50.818
I'm talking about when you give all
the control to the woman.

35:50.900 --> 35:52.740
- You relinquish the power.
- Right.

35:52.819 --> 35:54.739
- You give it all to the girl.
- Right.

35:54.862 --> 35:58.622
Right at that very moment is the time
that she will tear out your heart.

35:58.699 --> 36:01.829
She'll screw the milkman,
she'll get pregnant with a stranger.

36:01.911 --> 36:04.211
I'm telling you,
it's exactly what's happening

36:04.288 --> 36:07.828
and it's repeating itself
every relationship I have.

36:07.917 --> 36:08.917
It's the same.

36:09.001 --> 36:10.131
Truthfully, she wasn't your type.

36:10.211 --> 36:12.591
- Well, I wasn't finished.
- Look, enjoy your freedom.

36:12.755 --> 36:15.005
- Yeah, you wait till it happens to you.
- It has.

36:22.223 --> 36:23.223
Contact's late.

36:23.766 --> 36:25.346
All right, let's go.

36:26.018 --> 36:27.188
Chill.

36:30.231 --> 36:31.571
One of the nuts has legs.

36:32.066 --> 36:33.936
I hate this outfit. I hate this hat.

36:34.026 --> 36:35.026
Take it off.

36:49.250 --> 36:50.630
Have you ever been rejected?

36:54.380 --> 36:55.630
Would you be sad if I was dead?

37:00.595 --> 37:03.715
You're really pushing the boundaries
of our relationship, you know that?

37:18.362 --> 37:20.622
- Is that the contact?
- Could be.

37:23.618 --> 37:24.908
Too bad she's so homely.

37:24.994 --> 37:26.294
Stay focused.

37:29.624 --> 37:30.714
Are you the contact?

37:30.917 --> 37:32.457
I'm Sandra.

37:32.710 --> 37:33.790
What are your names?

37:34.045 --> 37:35.795
Buda, Pest.

37:40.051 --> 37:41.431
Follow me, please.

37:46.223 --> 37:48.313
Buda and Pest? Nice.

37:59.820 --> 38:01.820
Did you do all these?

38:03.324 --> 38:05.664
Yes. Take one.

38:06.160 --> 38:07.240
A gift.

38:07.370 --> 38:08.750
I don't take free gifts.

38:10.831 --> 38:12.541
- How much you want for it?
- Nothing.

38:12.625 --> 38:14.585
Taking money for something is not a gift.

38:15.169 --> 38:17.459
Taking nothing for something is.

38:18.047 --> 38:19.507
Is it like this all the time?

38:19.924 --> 38:22.184
This place was a beautiful place.

38:22.677 --> 38:27.007
Then one day, they came with money,
and General Garza sold his soul.

38:27.139 --> 38:28.809
And people who fight back are killed.

38:29.141 --> 38:30.391
You said "they" came with money.

38:30.476 --> 38:31.436
Who's "they"?

38:31.519 --> 38:33.349
Some Americans. That's all I know.

38:33.938 --> 38:36.228
But someday all of this will change back.

38:37.817 --> 38:38.937
You really believe that?

38:39.026 --> 38:40.106
Yes.

38:43.531 --> 38:44.781
You have a family, Sandra?

38:45.616 --> 38:47.946
My mother, when I was little, she died.

38:48.035 --> 38:50.955
And my father, he's gone, too.

38:51.872 --> 38:52.872
Do you?

38:52.999 --> 38:53.999
- Me?
- Yes.

38:54.083 --> 38:55.673
He has a truck and a seaplane.

38:59.839 --> 39:01.719
Sandra, how close
can you get to the palace?

39:01.799 --> 39:03.549
The palace? Why?

39:03.968 --> 39:06.218
We just wanna check out the view.

39:06.721 --> 39:07.851
There is no view.

39:07.930 --> 39:09.560
Why don't we just go there anyway, okay?

39:24.030 --> 39:25.320
Where is my grove?

39:26.741 --> 39:28.701
Where is your manpower?

39:33.497 --> 39:36.667
Do you know how long it takes
for a coca field to produce?

39:36.959 --> 39:38.379
Of course you don't. Let me tell you.

39:38.711 --> 39:40.671
We are eight weeks behind schedule.

39:40.963 --> 39:44.183
Kick your peasants' asses.
Get me my product.

39:44.425 --> 39:48.505
When you talk like this to me
in front of my men, it's no good.

39:50.431 --> 39:52.601
I am your lifeline.

39:52.808 --> 39:55.188
I am the one who coordinates
all this confusion.

39:55.394 --> 39:57.564
I am making you rich.

39:57.772 --> 39:59.822
And being wealthy is very good.

39:59.899 --> 40:03.939
It allows people to be the real asswipes
nature intended them to be.

40:08.574 --> 40:13.294
Sometimes things
are just not worth the money.

40:13.746 --> 40:14.746
Sure they are.

40:26.342 --> 40:28.682
Sandra, I was wondering about something
you were saying.

40:29.428 --> 40:30.968
- From a female point of view...
- What are you doing?

40:31.138 --> 40:34.348
Conversing. Look it up.
Out of curiosity,

40:34.475 --> 40:37.975
you ever have a person you liked
disrespect you in a bad way?

40:38.646 --> 40:39.856
Dis...

40:39.939 --> 40:42.069
I'm not sure what the Spanish is
for "disrespect."

40:42.316 --> 40:45.356
Come on. Why don't you man up? Jesus!

40:45.528 --> 40:46.528
She wasn't your type.

40:46.654 --> 40:49.074
Why don't you just keep saying,
"She wasn't my type?"

40:49.323 --> 40:51.493
So I could put a bullet in your bleak brain!

40:52.034 --> 40:54.584
Look who I'm talking to.
Dracula's life coach.

40:54.745 --> 40:56.115
No wonder you're alone.

40:56.747 --> 40:57.957
Sandra, are we close?

40:58.082 --> 40:59.252
It's just over there.

40:59.667 --> 41:01.037
- Pull over, please.
- Yeah, really.

41:08.092 --> 41:10.892
- Where is he going?
- I'm glad you asked.

41:11.512 --> 41:13.012
Well, I suppose you could say

41:13.180 --> 41:16.810
we like to look at the world
from different views.

41:20.187 --> 41:23.397
You... You got a black heart.

41:26.360 --> 41:27.530
She wasn't your type.

41:35.619 --> 41:36.789
We should get going.

41:37.538 --> 41:39.038
He's very emotional.

42:19.663 --> 42:21.673
What are you looking for?

42:25.085 --> 42:28.665
Sandra, how do I know
you're not setting us up?

42:29.340 --> 42:31.300
What does "setting us up" mean?

42:31.467 --> 42:33.757
You don't look like the kind of person
that we deal with all the time.

42:33.844 --> 42:35.934
How did you get involved in this?

42:36.222 --> 42:38.022
An American came here.

42:38.098 --> 42:42.138
He asked my friend to show you around.
He was afraid, so he asked me to.

42:42.269 --> 42:43.269
And you're not afraid?

42:43.437 --> 42:44.937
I'm afraid.

42:45.147 --> 42:47.397
But he said maybe you can help Vilena.

42:48.275 --> 42:49.855
I don't think so.

42:49.944 --> 42:50.954
Why not?

42:52.238 --> 42:53.408
To get this place going again,

42:53.489 --> 42:55.619
you have to rip the guts out of it
and start from the ground up

42:55.699 --> 42:58.289
and even I don't think
that's worth the money,

42:59.453 --> 43:02.373
so if I were you, I'd leave. Just leave.

43:11.006 --> 43:12.626
You should leave.

43:20.599 --> 43:22.349
Don't say anything. Let me talk.

43:56.093 --> 43:57.183
Run!

44:22.536 --> 44:23.786
- Get her.
- Got it.

44:37.885 --> 44:39.135
Are you crazy?

44:39.511 --> 44:41.561
- You could have killed me!
- You're welcome.

44:46.769 --> 44:47.769
What?

44:49.813 --> 44:52.573
All right, speed it up. We're on the way.

44:57.488 --> 44:58.988
If we get out of here, it's a miracle.

45:00.741 --> 45:02.581
- She's coming with us, right?
- She'd better.

45:05.412 --> 45:06.912
- How can we leave?
- We got a plane.

45:07.081 --> 45:09.581
- No, I can't leave.
- Yeah, well, you don't have a choice.

45:09.666 --> 45:11.626
- Yes, I do.
- Yeah? They'll find you in an hour.

45:11.794 --> 45:14.424
- Maybe, but I'm staying.
- Staying for what? There's nothing here.

45:14.630 --> 45:15.920
Not to you.

45:18.801 --> 45:20.931
Look, if you stay, then you're dead.
She's leaving with us.

46:08.976 --> 46:11.346
- I got the guys inside.
- Give me a 60-second lead.

46:11.437 --> 46:13.057
- You got it. Go, go, go!
- Come on.

46:29.705 --> 46:30.705
Get in.

46:31.999 --> 46:33.039
- Get in.
- No.

46:33.125 --> 46:34.665
- Get in.
- No, no, I can't.

46:34.751 --> 46:36.551
- Let's go.
- I can't. I belong here.

46:36.628 --> 46:38.708
- There's no time.
- Go, you go.

46:38.839 --> 46:40.009
Please, go.

46:40.674 --> 46:41.724
Shit.

46:59.359 --> 47:00.359
Hey!

47:02.362 --> 47:03.362
You look nervous.

47:26.720 --> 47:27.800
Come on!

47:43.570 --> 47:44.570
Come on!

47:50.369 --> 47:51.579
Run, you bastard!

48:28.657 --> 48:30.737
- Where's the girl?
- Gone. She wouldn't leave.

48:30.951 --> 48:32.491
Wouldn't leave?

48:32.578 --> 48:34.448
Why the hell would anybody wanna stay?

48:44.631 --> 48:45.971
The hell...

48:48.552 --> 48:49.972
The hell With it.

48:50.053 --> 48:52.643
- Climb, baby, climb.
- Come on, baby.

49:04.526 --> 49:05.526
God damn it.

49:13.994 --> 49:15.374
- Going back?
- Yeah.

49:15.537 --> 49:17.617
- Fry and die.
- Fry and die. Let's do it.

50:29.903 --> 50:31.363
What are they doing?

50:51.007 --> 50:52.087
Yes!

51:03.770 --> 51:04.940
Great job.

51:05.939 --> 51:07.109
That was a statement!

51:25.625 --> 51:29.245
How did two obvious professionals
pass right through security personnel,

51:29.337 --> 51:31.757
kill 41 soldiers and get away?

51:32.883 --> 51:34.553
With help, that's how.

51:35.218 --> 51:37.798
Everything's under control,
except one detail,

51:38.472 --> 51:42.022
a daughter who wants her father
and company dead and gone.

51:42.142 --> 51:43.772
Bad Shakespeare.

51:44.269 --> 51:47.019
Somehow the company parasites got to her.

51:47.147 --> 51:48.817
Look, she's your daughter, and that's tragic.

51:50.692 --> 51:52.822
But blood or not, she goes.

51:53.653 --> 51:55.413
Call it the price of doing business.

51:56.198 --> 51:57.988
<i>You don't kill your familia.</i>

51:58.575 --> 52:01.365
Come around my house
during the holidays, pal.

52:21.348 --> 52:22.678
Nice bird.

52:23.683 --> 52:25.483
First of all, I don't feel comfortable

52:25.560 --> 52:28.150
talking business with a giant
carrying a shotgun.

52:28.271 --> 52:29.611
Pretty boy wouldn't give it up.

52:30.065 --> 52:31.225
Not if you wanna know where they are.

52:31.691 --> 52:32.691
What do you know?

52:33.068 --> 52:34.068
I used to be one of them.

52:38.824 --> 52:39.834
Why are you turning on them?

52:40.033 --> 52:41.373
Lovers' quarrel.

52:42.619 --> 52:43.619
We settle on 50.

52:43.703 --> 52:45.213
No, math whiz.

52:45.539 --> 52:48.289
We settle on 100 grand,
upfront, in my pocket.

52:48.875 --> 52:50.585
The guy thinks he's a real badass.

52:50.877 --> 52:52.497
Actually, I'm a horror show.

52:55.632 --> 52:57.302
This geezer's a bloody joke

52:57.425 --> 52:58.675
Life's a joke, gum-chew.

53:00.554 --> 53:03.724
I've been standing in a space
about the size of your mouth for six hours.

53:04.057 --> 53:06.387
If you don't want that Fu Manchu
knocked back into the '60s,

53:06.476 --> 53:09.806
you'd better keep your gum-chewing trap
shut and show some respect!

53:10.397 --> 53:11.517
Hey.

53:12.399 --> 53:14.279
Need a facelift, pretty boy?

53:14.901 --> 53:16.151
Bring it.

53:17.195 --> 53:18.235
Back off, Paine.

53:18.321 --> 53:19.321
I'm gonna kill him.

53:19.406 --> 53:20.616
We need him.

53:22.367 --> 53:23.617
Back off!

53:28.748 --> 53:30.458
Here's what I think is happening.

53:30.542 --> 53:33.922
This guy who calls himself Church
is really a front for the CIA.

53:34.087 --> 53:36.047
So we're working for the agency?

53:36.256 --> 53:38.546
Yeah.
Church hired us to take out the General,

53:38.633 --> 53:41.603
but the real target's this guy,
James Munroe.

53:43.597 --> 53:45.927
He used to be with the agency,
but got greedy,

53:46.016 --> 53:47.596
went rogue and teamed up with the General

53:47.684 --> 53:50.024
to keep the whole drug operation
for themselves.

53:50.103 --> 53:52.113
And that's a big cash loss.

53:52.188 --> 53:55.148
But Church and the agency
can't afford to send in the Navy SEALs

53:55.233 --> 53:57.943
or the Special Forces
to take out one of their own.

53:58.194 --> 54:01.204
That'd be a bad headline,
so they hire us to kill him.

54:02.365 --> 54:03.775
And they're back in business.

54:03.992 --> 54:06.122
- And we're taken out.
- Nobody's gonna miss us.

54:07.495 --> 54:09.615
- Is it still $5 million?
- You'd never live to spend it.

54:09.956 --> 54:11.116
I'm telling Church the deal's off.

54:12.876 --> 54:14.416
Sound about right?

54:14.502 --> 54:15.632
That's about right.

54:15.712 --> 54:16.712
I agree.

54:42.822 --> 54:44.072
You still got the helmet?

54:46.952 --> 54:48.162
Where is he?

55:01.925 --> 55:04.215
- Who the hell is that?
- Some punk.

55:04.803 --> 55:06.853
- Don't worry about it.
- We got your back.

55:07.347 --> 55:10.177
If he comes over here, we'll bust his ass.

55:16.731 --> 55:17.861
What do you want?

55:19.192 --> 55:20.442
Your life.

55:21.444 --> 55:22.574
I was thinking about taking it.

55:22.654 --> 55:23.664
Is that right?

55:23.780 --> 55:27.870
But I don't do so well in tight spaces,
so going to prison worries me.

55:29.077 --> 55:30.287
You shouldn't have bruised her face.

55:30.537 --> 55:31.537
Really?

55:31.621 --> 55:33.421
I would have liked to have kept it
the way it was.

55:33.873 --> 55:35.293
Keep the bitch, 'cause I'm done with it.

56:07.282 --> 56:08.372
Lee.

56:13.913 --> 56:17.633
Next time, I'll deflate all your balls, friend.

56:27.427 --> 56:29.887
Now you know what I do for a living.

56:30.638 --> 56:32.348
I'm not perfect, but you should have waited.

56:34.100 --> 56:35.810
I was worth it.

57:44.337 --> 57:45.837
Where is she?

58:01.187 --> 58:02.857
So your daughter paints, too?

58:03.857 --> 58:05.527
This is how it starts!

58:05.859 --> 58:07.319
There's nothing here. Let's go.

58:07.402 --> 58:08.952
Or how it ends!

58:45.064 --> 58:48.154
What's the matter, Barney?
Don't you ever sleep?

58:48.234 --> 58:50.154
No. What happened to your girlfriend?

58:50.737 --> 58:53.357
Another one bites the dust, brother.

58:54.240 --> 58:58.660
I was gonna paint this for her,
and you know what? I'm gonna finish it.

58:58.870 --> 59:01.080
Then I'm just gonna smash the shit
out of it.

59:01.372 --> 59:02.462
You wanna be alone?

59:04.417 --> 59:06.537
Not really. So, what's up?

59:06.920 --> 59:08.590
On this island, there was this girl.

59:08.922 --> 59:11.092
There usually are.

59:11.257 --> 59:16.007
You know, she showed us around.
She was the target's daughter.

59:17.805 --> 59:21.635
And when she had a chance to leave,
she didn't do it.

59:23.019 --> 59:24.939
She had some guts.

59:26.397 --> 59:28.857
Why can't I get that out of my mind?

59:30.443 --> 59:32.323
You know, she stands for something.

59:32.779 --> 59:34.409
You know, man, we don't stand for shit.

59:34.489 --> 59:39.699
We used to, but that dried all up,
like this is gonna dry all up.

59:39.869 --> 59:42.119
This here paint is gonna dry.

59:43.122 --> 59:44.462
What dried up?

59:46.960 --> 59:49.420
Just belief, man. Just the belief in the soul,

59:49.504 --> 59:52.594
just, I don't know,
the human parts, brother.

59:54.133 --> 59:56.303
You remember that time
we was up in Bosnia?

59:57.220 --> 1:00:00.560
We took down them Serb bad boys.

1:00:02.934 --> 1:00:06.194
All our guys were getting chopped up
all around us,

1:00:07.146 --> 1:00:08.976
and there was blood everywhere.

1:00:09.065 --> 1:00:10.815
I never thought I was gonna make it
out of there,

1:00:10.900 --> 1:00:13.490
-and I know you didn't, either.
- Yeah.

1:00:13.569 --> 1:00:17.119
Kind of feeling like dead, too, you know?

1:00:17.198 --> 1:00:19.948
My head's all a very black place.

1:00:20.034 --> 1:00:22.004
I don't believe in shit.

1:00:22.870 --> 1:00:25.710
Just goddamn Dracula black.

1:00:26.916 --> 1:00:31.586
I remember I got this bottle of the local shit
they have over there, that Slivovitz.

1:00:31.671 --> 1:00:34.841
I don't know,
I think that's what it was called.

1:00:35.675 --> 1:00:37.755
And I ain't feeling no pain now.

1:00:39.387 --> 1:00:40.847
And I'd come up on this...

1:00:42.557 --> 1:00:45.437
I'd come up on this old wooden bridge,
and I see this...

1:00:46.769 --> 1:00:48.269
I see this...

1:00:51.399 --> 1:00:54.899
I see this woman standing there, you know?
And she's...

1:00:56.446 --> 1:00:57.986
I stepped out, and she saw me,

1:00:58.072 --> 1:01:02.742
and she's just looking right in my eyes,
and I was looking right in her eyes.

1:01:04.454 --> 1:01:06.414
I knew what she was gonna do.

1:01:06.497 --> 1:01:09.957
She looked at me,
and I knew she was gonna jump.

1:01:11.210 --> 1:01:12.250
You know what I did, man?

1:01:12.337 --> 1:01:17.547
I just turned around and I kept walking,
until I heard that splash.

1:01:21.346 --> 1:01:23.006
Then she was gone.

1:01:24.849 --> 1:01:27.229
And after taking all them lives,

1:01:27.393 --> 1:01:32.943
here was one that I could have saved,
but I didn't.

1:01:35.526 --> 1:01:37.896
And what I realized later on was,

1:01:40.239 --> 1:01:43.529
if I had saved that woman, I might have,

1:01:45.995 --> 1:01:48.705
I don't know,
saved what was left of my soul, you know?

1:02:23.408 --> 1:02:24.618
Sandra,

1:02:25.660 --> 1:02:28.750
short for Alexsandra,
which is Latin for "Defender of mankind,"

1:02:28.830 --> 1:02:30.000
and, bingo, here you are.

1:02:30.081 --> 1:02:31.371
Now that's synergy.

1:02:33.668 --> 1:02:35.248
You're not following that.

1:02:35.670 --> 1:02:40.170
And I know you're probably not,
illiteracy being 98% in your country.

1:02:40.258 --> 1:02:41.628
Try following this.

1:02:42.301 --> 1:02:48.561
A very wise dead man once told me
that a real man never strikes a woman.

1:02:49.976 --> 1:02:54.306
You push some if you have to,
but you never strike them.

1:02:55.982 --> 1:02:59.072
This man, however,
does not share that moral dilemma.

1:02:59.986 --> 1:03:04.986
So the question, Sandra,
why were the Americans here?

1:03:52.872 --> 1:03:54.712
Don't fight back.

1:03:56.334 --> 1:03:57.844
Just relax.

1:04:29.033 --> 1:04:31.913
Again, what did the Americans tell you?

1:04:32.495 --> 1:04:34.075
Who were they after?

1:04:36.874 --> 1:04:38.294
Continue.

1:05:05.319 --> 1:05:06.649
You wanted answers.

1:05:06.779 --> 1:05:07.909
Not like that!

1:05:08.406 --> 1:05:09.776
Whatever you say.

1:05:22.420 --> 1:05:25.300
- I'm going back to Vilena.
- Yeah? Something change?

1:05:25.464 --> 1:05:27.174
- What's the plan?
- There is no plan.

1:05:27.300 --> 1:05:30.680
- Wait, wait, wait. We need a strategy.
- I'm going. You're not.

1:05:30.761 --> 1:05:33.431
- What?
- I said I'm going. You guys aren't.

1:05:33.639 --> 1:05:36.389
- What are you, out of your mind?
- It's personal business.

1:05:36.475 --> 1:05:39.055
- You don't owe that woman nothing.
- I didn't say I did.

1:05:39.145 --> 1:05:41.185
You want to kill yourself? Go ahead, fine.
Your call.

1:05:41.272 --> 1:05:44.282
Listen, I don't want to kill myself.
You guys, take care. I got to do this.

1:05:44.358 --> 1:05:46.278
- Hey, hey, hey.
- What?

1:05:46.360 --> 1:05:48.110
Don't lay this guilt crap on us.
We don't deserve it.

1:05:48.195 --> 1:05:52.735
This is my choice. There's no guilt.
There's no guilt. Take care.

1:05:58.414 --> 1:06:01.254
Yeah, fuck it. His choice. Yeah.

1:06:10.343 --> 1:06:11.473
I said I'm going alone.

1:06:11.552 --> 1:06:12.552
I'm going, too.

1:06:12.762 --> 1:06:14.562
Come on, Yang, get the hell out.

1:06:14.722 --> 1:06:16.182
Just drive.

1:06:25.775 --> 1:06:28.025
Don't lose your nerve.

1:06:29.654 --> 1:06:31.864
Don't talk to me, cockroach.

1:06:43.459 --> 1:06:45.499
So, why are you doing this?

1:06:45.586 --> 1:06:47.296
Friends die together.

1:06:49.048 --> 1:06:51.338
Hey. Give me the good luck ring. Come on.

1:06:52.593 --> 1:06:54.263
Don't make me hurt you, Yang. Come on.

1:06:54.637 --> 1:06:57.427
- Speed better than luck.
- Whatever.

1:06:59.225 --> 1:07:00.265
It's difficult.

1:07:00.726 --> 1:07:01.726
What is?

1:07:02.019 --> 1:07:04.019
My life is difficult. I need more money.

1:07:04.188 --> 1:07:05.148
Why is that?

1:07:05.231 --> 1:07:07.271
- I work harder than the rest.
- No, you don't.

1:07:07.400 --> 1:07:12.030
Yes, I do. Because they're taller,
everything is harder for me.

1:07:12.113 --> 1:07:16.413
When I get hurt, the wound is bigger
because I'm smaller.

1:07:17.243 --> 1:07:19.083
When I travel, I need to go farther.

1:07:19.161 --> 1:07:20.581
I know, 'cause you're smaller, right?

1:07:21.080 --> 1:07:22.160
Yes.

1:07:24.083 --> 1:07:25.383
My life is harder than you think.

1:07:27.586 --> 1:07:30.836
- I need more money.
- I know. You told me.

1:07:30.923 --> 1:07:32.303
For your family, right?

1:07:32.508 --> 1:07:33.758
I don't have family.

1:07:33.926 --> 1:07:35.426
I know.

1:07:36.512 --> 1:07:37.812
Maybe one day I will.

1:07:38.889 --> 1:07:40.139
Down!

1:08:06.542 --> 1:08:08.042
- Get out there!
- Why me?

1:08:08.252 --> 1:08:09.382
Because you're smaller.

1:08:27.313 --> 1:08:28.443
Do that again, I'll kill you!

1:09:04.850 --> 1:09:06.060
Gunner!

1:09:11.649 --> 1:09:12.649
Come on, Gunner.

1:09:14.193 --> 1:09:15.193
Man's good.

1:09:48.727 --> 1:09:51.807
What are you doing? You're dead, junkie!

1:09:58.028 --> 1:09:59.238
Insect

1:10:13.002 --> 1:10:14.092
Bail!

1:10:22.928 --> 1:10:24.178
Shit!

1:10:53.042 --> 1:10:54.132
Yang!

1:10:54.877 --> 1:10:56.667
Come out, come out, wherever you are!

1:10:58.130 --> 1:10:59.510
It's over!

1:10:59.715 --> 1:11:01.295
Let's talk about this.
I forgive you, Yang!

1:11:06.347 --> 1:11:07.467
That almost hurt.

1:11:07.932 --> 1:11:08.932
Back off!

1:11:16.106 --> 1:11:18.816
What do you wear, size three?
Bring it, happy feet.

1:11:49.598 --> 1:11:50.638
Come on, bring it!

1:12:29.096 --> 1:12:30.136
Size matters.

1:12:39.732 --> 1:12:40.732
Gunner!

1:12:40.816 --> 1:12:41.976
Hello, karma!

1:12:47.865 --> 1:12:48.945
Shit!

1:13:17.644 --> 1:13:19.104
You shot me.

1:13:20.064 --> 1:13:22.574
Hey, don't say that.
You were gonna kill him.

1:13:22.900 --> 1:13:24.490
No, I was just gonna scare him.

1:13:24.777 --> 1:13:27.487
Don't say that. You never liked him.
You were gonna kill him.

1:13:28.113 --> 1:13:29.573
That's true.

1:13:35.245 --> 1:13:36.535
Am I dying?

1:13:37.122 --> 1:13:39.002
The shot's a couple of inches
above your heart.

1:13:42.211 --> 1:13:45.511
Gunner, who sent you? Who hired you?

1:13:46.924 --> 1:13:48.304
Who cares?

1:13:48.383 --> 1:13:49.893
Who cares? I care.

1:13:50.469 --> 1:13:55.139
Don't go out a total asshole.
For once, cooperate.

1:13:55.641 --> 1:13:59.311
Who sent you? Who hired you?
Tell me. Let me make it right.

1:14:00.187 --> 1:14:01.607
Bury me right.

1:14:02.856 --> 1:14:04.606
And I want a Viking funeral.

1:14:06.985 --> 1:14:09.485
You mean where they put you in a boat
and set you on fire, Viking?

1:14:09.571 --> 1:14:11.491
- That's right!
- You're not a Viking.

1:14:12.074 --> 1:14:13.834
So what? Who cares?

1:14:14.159 --> 1:14:17.079
If that's what you want, you got it.

1:14:17.496 --> 1:14:20.116
Who sent you? ls the girl still alive?

1:14:20.290 --> 1:14:21.330
Come closer.

1:14:40.644 --> 1:14:42.354
You know, it's not easy being your friend.

1:14:43.063 --> 1:14:44.273
That's true.

1:14:44.356 --> 1:14:46.856
Man, we'll die with you.
Just don't ask us to do it twice.

1:14:47.359 --> 1:14:49.859
I know the layout.
I'll tell you about it on the way.

1:14:51.029 --> 1:14:52.659
What the hell happened to you?

1:14:52.739 --> 1:14:54.199
It's too sad to talk about it.

1:14:57.953 --> 1:14:59.293
Let's fly.

1:15:16.680 --> 1:15:19.770
You know, the enemy's
always been terrified of noise,

1:15:20.100 --> 1:15:21.890
especially shotguns.

1:15:23.312 --> 1:15:25.902
With this big boy spitting out
250 rounds a minute,

1:15:25.981 --> 1:15:27.691
you tell me who's tolerating that.

1:15:29.985 --> 1:15:32.775
You know what? I trust you.

1:15:33.530 --> 1:15:35.070
I want you to meet my girlfriend.

1:15:35.365 --> 1:15:38.195
Omya Kaboom.

1:15:38.410 --> 1:15:40.700
When Omya's prime is struck,

1:15:41.371 --> 1:15:44.711
she gets off a miniature warhead
that arms itself.

1:15:44.917 --> 1:15:47.877
And when that happens,
anything that gets in my lady's way

1:15:47.961 --> 1:15:50.671
becomes instant red sauce and Jell-O.

1:15:50.756 --> 1:15:52.006
And if that doesn't work

1:15:56.261 --> 1:15:58.011
her sister will.

1:16:00.098 --> 1:16:03.598
So let me get this right.
Gunner tries to kill you, you shoot him

1:16:03.936 --> 1:16:05.766
and, at death's door,
he gives you the whole layout?

1:16:05.938 --> 1:16:07.018
Something like that.

1:16:07.105 --> 1:16:09.185
But I had to promise him this Viking funeral.

1:16:09.274 --> 1:16:11.284
You know, where you have to
spread the ashes over the ocean.

1:16:12.110 --> 1:16:14.030
What a way to poison
about a thousand whales.

1:16:14.112 --> 1:16:15.362
At least.

1:16:17.407 --> 1:16:19.487
Listen, we owe the big bastard a send-off.

1:16:19.952 --> 1:16:22.002
- I would have win.
- I know you would have win.

1:16:22.079 --> 1:16:24.539
<i>Mumbo jumbo, hoodoo lady, hoodoo</i>

1:16:24.790 --> 1:16:30.250
<i>Mumbo jumbo, hoodoo lady, hoodoo</i>

1:16:30.420 --> 1:16:33.380
<i>Boom-lay, boom-lay, boom-lay, boom!</i>

1:16:38.470 --> 1:16:39.470
More like a million whales.

1:18:02.512 --> 1:18:04.892
It's 3:36. We have 20 minutes
to take this place down.

1:18:04.973 --> 1:18:06.813
I'll take the cellar.

1:18:06.892 --> 1:18:08.192
We've got company.

1:18:09.394 --> 1:18:10.694
I got him. You guys take off.

1:18:39.174 --> 1:18:41.894
Is there a reason you've taken
the soldiers this man has trained

1:18:41.968 --> 1:18:44.388
and made them look like fools?

1:18:45.263 --> 1:18:47.523
They look like warriors.

1:18:51.770 --> 1:18:53.940
Warriors loyal to me.

1:18:55.440 --> 1:18:59.400
I thought the people of Vilena
hired these mercenaries to kill me.

1:19:00.779 --> 1:19:05.279
But then I think maybe this is your plan,
because you cannot control me.

1:19:05.742 --> 1:19:08.832
And torturing Sandra works for you.

1:19:09.788 --> 1:19:12.498
You want to kill her to make me suffer.

1:19:14.042 --> 1:19:17.302
A man can never kill a child.

1:19:18.463 --> 1:19:19.633
But you can.

1:19:20.132 --> 1:19:21.552
You're losing your mind.

1:19:22.134 --> 1:19:25.224
You do not control me!

1:19:27.639 --> 1:19:29.559
Bring Sandra here.

1:19:30.642 --> 1:19:34.482
Bring her now or I will kill you.

1:19:34.813 --> 1:19:36.023
Go get her.

1:22:35.327 --> 1:22:39.247
- No, no.
- Sandra, Sandra, it's me. Sandra.

1:22:39.873 --> 1:22:43.253
Hey, it's me, it's me. Sandra, it's me.

1:22:43.835 --> 1:22:46.665
It's me. It's me. It's okay.

1:22:47.964 --> 1:22:50.134
Nobody's gonna hurt you, all right?

1:22:50.216 --> 1:22:51.376
How are you here?

1:22:51.968 --> 1:22:53.008
I just am.

1:22:55.180 --> 1:22:57.020
- Can you move?
- Yes.

1:22:57.599 --> 1:22:58.599
Okay.

1:22:58.683 --> 1:23:00.943
Yeah, okay. All right, let's go.

1:23:15.950 --> 1:23:18.580
- Get off.
- Let's see what you got here.

1:23:19.371 --> 1:23:20.711
Nice.

1:23:21.373 --> 1:23:22.623
Goddamn.

1:23:23.041 --> 1:23:26.461
I'm having these babies, seeing as
you ain't gonna need them any more.

1:23:32.801 --> 1:23:34.591
All right, I'm gonna ask you a few questions.

1:23:36.096 --> 1:23:37.556
You're gonna give me answers.

1:23:38.848 --> 1:23:40.808
If they're not the right answers, you will die.

1:23:42.894 --> 1:23:44.104
Why are you here?

1:23:45.313 --> 1:23:46.363
Bird watching.

1:23:49.651 --> 1:23:50.901
Bird watching.

1:23:52.570 --> 1:23:54.070
Stop him!

1:23:54.406 --> 1:23:56.406
- This is not his fight. It's mine.
- Get her out of here.

1:23:57.617 --> 1:23:59.037
Seal the building.

1:24:01.371 --> 1:24:02.621
You're a real tough guy, aren't you?

1:24:02.956 --> 1:24:04.076
What?

1:24:09.254 --> 1:24:10.264
Time's up.

1:24:10.338 --> 1:24:11.668
- Where's Barney?
- What's the call?

1:24:11.923 --> 1:24:12.923
We can't find him in 10 minutes,

1:24:13.007 --> 1:24:14.007
we're going out the same way we came in.

1:24:14.092 --> 1:24:15.092
- No way.
- That's what he'd want.

1:24:15.218 --> 1:24:17.298
Ten minutes! Let's go.

1:24:21.558 --> 1:24:23.388
Hi. What's your name?

1:24:23.852 --> 1:24:25.692
- You having fun yet, mate?
- Yeah, not bad.

1:24:25.812 --> 1:24:27.272
Personally, I'm glad you came back.

1:24:27.439 --> 1:24:28.439
Yeah?

1:24:31.818 --> 1:24:32.818
Get him up.

1:24:35.947 --> 1:24:37.447
Stand him up.

1:24:41.619 --> 1:24:44.039
You know,
if you didn't have this Kevlar vest,

1:24:44.372 --> 1:24:46.542
your insides are gonna be
like fucking mush.

1:24:46.750 --> 1:24:47.920
Well, ain't that sad?

1:24:48.251 --> 1:24:49.211
You know, you're a lucky man.

1:24:49.294 --> 1:24:50.754
You're the lucky man.

1:24:50.879 --> 1:24:52.959
No, no, you're a lucky man.

1:24:53.840 --> 1:24:55.970
- He told me to keep you conscious.
- Did he?

1:24:58.178 --> 1:24:59.928
All right. All right.

1:25:03.975 --> 1:25:05.385
Now this is your last time.

1:25:05.685 --> 1:25:09.145
You give me the right answer,
and I'll cut you a break.

1:25:11.107 --> 1:25:14.067
If you give me the wrong answer,
you will die a damn slow death.

1:25:14.152 --> 1:25:15.702
Do you understand me?

1:25:15.779 --> 1:25:17.569
- Do you understand me?
- Yep.

1:25:17.655 --> 1:25:20.325
- Who sent you?
- Can't breathe.

1:25:20.784 --> 1:25:22.244
Loosen up.

1:25:22.911 --> 1:25:24.161
Who sent you?

1:25:26.664 --> 1:25:28.674
Your hairdresser.

1:26:31.229 --> 1:26:32.689
You're good.

1:27:50.808 --> 1:27:51.848
Go, we gotta go!

1:28:12.830 --> 1:28:14.580
Come on.

1:28:38.356 --> 1:28:39.516
Shit!

1:29:01.379 --> 1:29:02.669
Remember this shit at Christmas!

1:29:06.426 --> 1:29:07.426
Damn, that thing's loud.

1:29:07.510 --> 1:29:10.050
- What happened to you?
- I got my ass kicked.

1:29:14.100 --> 1:29:15.230
Damn, that stings!

1:29:15.601 --> 1:29:16.641
Suck it up!

1:29:16.728 --> 1:29:18.228
Come on. Get my rifle. Let's go.

1:29:38.332 --> 1:29:39.462
What's this?

1:29:41.794 --> 1:29:44.464
Everything bad that has happened,
you bring.

1:29:44.547 --> 1:29:46.127
Take your money!

1:29:47.258 --> 1:29:50.428
I only see death with you. Take it all and go.

1:29:50.762 --> 1:29:51.972
I'm not going anywhere.

1:29:52.055 --> 1:29:53.305
You are done here.

1:29:53.389 --> 1:29:54.679
You can't succeed without me.

1:29:54.891 --> 1:29:56.021
I am the leader.

1:29:56.184 --> 1:29:57.314
You're a puppet in a hat.

1:29:59.395 --> 1:30:00.395
No.

1:30:19.290 --> 1:30:20.540
Now!

1:30:23.586 --> 1:30:24.916
Get back.

1:30:27.965 --> 1:30:29.125
This shit's getting old.

1:30:34.305 --> 1:30:35.765
<i>Throw down your weapons.</i>

1:30:37.350 --> 1:30:38.890
<i>There's no way out.</i>

1:30:41.354 --> 1:30:43.524
- Your lucky ring stinks.
- I know.

1:30:44.023 --> 1:30:45.613
- Let's backtrack.
- The building's rigged.

1:30:45.691 --> 1:30:47.571
It's the only way out.

1:30:58.329 --> 1:30:59.459
Chopper's ready in five minutes.

1:30:59.539 --> 1:31:00.579
We're not leaving yet.

1:31:10.383 --> 1:31:13.143
- What's he saying?
- He said we're dead with an accent.

1:31:13.219 --> 1:31:14.599
We ain't dead.

1:31:14.679 --> 1:31:16.349
- Blow the building.
- Not yet.

1:31:16.514 --> 1:31:20.024
We will kill this American disease.

1:31:37.702 --> 1:31:39.042
Blow the building!

1:31:39.120 --> 1:31:40.250
She's still in there!

1:31:40.496 --> 1:31:41.996
The money!

1:31:47.336 --> 1:31:48.376
Blow it!

1:31:52.967 --> 1:31:53.967
Blow it!

1:32:00.099 --> 1:32:03.059
She's out. Blow the fucking building!

1:33:46.998 --> 1:33:48.458
I'm out!

1:34:44.555 --> 1:34:46.215
Let's go. Come on.

1:34:47.224 --> 1:34:48.604
Cut Munroe off!

1:35:48.911 --> 1:35:50.001
Come on!

1:37:05.029 --> 1:37:06.029
Hey!

1:37:06.530 --> 1:37:07.820
- Thing's too heavy.
- Give me it.

1:37:07.907 --> 1:37:10.617
- What do you want me to do?
- Throw it as hard as you can.

1:37:35.935 --> 1:37:37.685
- Blow the dump.
- Got it!

1:38:10.386 --> 1:38:11.426
Munroe!

1:38:12.930 --> 1:38:16.350
Drop the weapons,
or I'll put a bullet through her eye.

1:38:18.769 --> 1:38:19.849
Don't test me.

1:38:30.906 --> 1:38:32.236
No,no,no.

1:38:32.408 --> 1:38:34.738
Shut up or I'll kill you.

1:38:36.787 --> 1:38:39.667
The agency parasites hired you,
didn't they?

1:38:39.748 --> 1:38:43.588
I'd have paid you twice as much
to go fishing.

1:38:44.128 --> 1:38:46.628
You'd have to think
I'm pretty freaking stupid

1:38:46.714 --> 1:38:48.474
to surrender to the agency.

1:38:48.591 --> 1:38:53.351
Why would I do that? I created this.
I made it all happen.

1:38:53.721 --> 1:38:57.851
And then they wanted me out. Why?
Because I saw the big picture.

1:38:58.142 --> 1:39:01.772
Unlike people like her father, you,
the agency,

1:39:02.396 --> 1:39:04.316
you see life through a freaking keyhole

1:39:04.398 --> 1:39:06.858
because you let emotions
cloud your judgment.

1:39:07.443 --> 1:39:10.703
Emotions are the cancer of the intellect!

1:39:10.863 --> 1:39:12.033
Stop walking.

1:39:13.824 --> 1:39:17.494
And what about me and you?
We're both the same.

1:39:17.953 --> 1:39:21.543
We're both mercenaries.
We're both dead inside.

1:39:22.708 --> 1:39:24.338
So why the hell did you come after me?

1:39:24.585 --> 1:39:27.205
I didn't come after you, dipshit.
I came for her!

1:39:47.232 --> 1:39:48.942
- You okay?
- Yeah.

1:39:49.735 --> 1:39:51.395
Call it a tie.

1:39:53.864 --> 1:39:55.204
Yeah, I guess so.

1:39:55.783 --> 1:39:57.873
You know, you're not as fast as you think.

1:39:58.369 --> 1:40:00.079
I'm beginning to sense that.

1:40:41.412 --> 1:40:45.082
The second account number's mine.
It'll help get things going around here.

1:40:45.416 --> 1:40:47.956
No, I can't. You've done so much.

1:40:48.043 --> 1:40:51.593
Yeah, well, so have you. A gift for a gift.
You take it.

1:40:52.423 --> 1:40:56.393
- Will you come back?
- I promise I'll always be around.

1:41:01.765 --> 1:41:02.885
Take care.

1:41:32.296 --> 1:41:33.296
What?

1:41:34.006 --> 1:41:35.006
Truthfully?

1:41:35.632 --> 1:41:36.632
Yeah?

1:41:37.259 --> 1:41:39.139
I never really thought she was your type.

1:42:04.495 --> 1:42:06.325
All right, baby. All right.

1:42:06.413 --> 1:42:07.793
Come on, let's see what you got.

1:42:10.417 --> 1:42:11.707
That's my boy!

1:42:16.048 --> 1:42:17.218
Go south!

1:42:23.138 --> 1:42:24.808
You lost! You lost!

1:42:28.602 --> 1:42:31.062
So you're back from the dead.
How you healing?

1:42:31.522 --> 1:42:34.982
Good, considering
you could have killed me.

1:42:35.484 --> 1:42:36.694
I forgive you.

1:42:37.194 --> 1:42:38.494
Okay.

1:42:39.071 --> 1:42:40.071
I would have win.

1:42:41.281 --> 1:42:42.451
Never.

1:42:45.536 --> 1:42:46.946
Hey, Gunner.

1:42:47.204 --> 1:42:50.124
Whatever doesn't kill you
makes you stronger, brother. Therapy.

1:42:51.083 --> 1:42:52.883
- What's he saying?
- He said try therapy.

1:42:55.879 --> 1:42:56.959
Man's got a point.

1:43:04.263 --> 1:43:05.393
You know what?

1:43:06.348 --> 1:43:08.058
I'm gonna do you a favor, Tool.

1:43:08.892 --> 1:43:11.142
"I once knew a man called Tool..."

1:43:11.520 --> 1:43:13.270
I love poetry.

1:43:13.689 --> 1:43:17.069
"To me, was the epitome of cool

1:43:18.443 --> 1:43:19.653
"He was good with a knife

1:43:22.698 --> 1:43:24.408
"Bad With a Wife..."

1:43:25.742 --> 1:43:26.742
That hurts.

1:43:26.910 --> 1:43:29.160
"But to think he could beat me

1:43:30.205 --> 1:43:33.325
"Dreaming he'd defeat me

1:43:34.835 --> 1:43:36.165
"Cool Tool

1:43:38.505 --> 1:43:39.585
"You gotta be a fool"

1:43:43.969 --> 1:43:45.259
Oh, yeah.
